      • testDateLongSubstitution

        public void testDateLongSubstitution()
                              throws java.lang.Exception
        Instantiate off of each others JSON String, proving Date for long substitution works. This will work on any field that is of type Date or Long. It will not work when the Dates are inside a Collection, for example.

        This substitution trick allows Date fields to be converted to long in order to save memory 16 bytes of memory per date. (Date's are more than 8 bytes, longs are 8).

        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
